{"first_name":"Peter","last_name":"Radsliff","permalink":"peter-radsliff","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/peter-radsliff","homepage_url":"http://www.presto.com","birthplace":"San Rafael","twitter_username":"prestoceo","blog_url":"http://blog.presto.com","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"Presto Services","born_year":1957,"born_month":4,"born_day":30,"tag_list":"peter-radsliff","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Mon Apr 12 06:06:02 UTC 2010","updated_at":"Tue Apr 13 19:00:59 UTC 2010","overview":"<p>Peter Radsliff is currently President &amp; CEO of Presto Services Inc. The company is the developer of Presto Mail, a solution that allows family members to email messages, photos and documents to elder family members who don&#8217;t use a computer or have Internet service. The company is funded by Kleiner Perkins Caufield Byers, Clearstone Venture Partners, Vanguard Ventures and Advanced Equities Inc. </p>\n\n<p>Radsliff has been an executive at four venture-backed startups: Presto, Data Robotics (f.k.a. Trusted Data Corp.), Mirra, Inc. and Sage Systems, Inc. These companies were funded by Greylock Partners, Sequoia Capital &amp; VSP Capital, and Cardinal Venture Capital respectively. He also became an executive at Seagate Technologies after their acquisition of Mirra and was head of marketing and product development at Monster Cable Products for 7.5 years.</p>\n\n<p>Prior to his work at startups and in consumer electronics, he worked for 10 years in different capacities at the scuba diving equipment manufacturing company Oceanic, learning many aspects of engineering, design and marketing. </p>\n\n<p>Radsliff has also taught graduate and core design courses at San Francisco State University and has guest lectured there and at Santa Clara University. </p>","image":{"available_sizes":[[[150,150],"assets/images/resized/0008/3435/83435v2-max-150x150.jpg"],[[250,250],"assets/images/resized/0008/3435/83435v2-max-250x250.jpg"],[[450,450],"assets/images/resi